The paper deals with the analysis of the dynamics and geometry of hidden states in a recurrent neural network for a classification task. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and specifically deals with neural networks (cs.NE) and their implementation for classification tasks (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of RNNs for natural language processing (cs.CL) and image classification (cs.CV), which are both relevant sub-categories.
